        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " That certain persons were enjoined to salute the other members of the Church is a proof that the Epistle was given into the hands of the presbyters. The reference is to the mode of salutation in the East. The kiss is called \"holy\" because it was the symbol of Christian affection. The same exhortation is made in other Epistles (",
        "children": []
